  ],
  "text": "ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable is defined in raft/storage.go (lines 36-38) as an error returned by the Storage interface's Snapshot() method when the required snapshot is temporarily unavailable. The error indicates that the raft state machine should retry calling Snapshot() later as the storage needs time to prepare the snapshot.\n\nThe snapshot availability check during Raft log catch-up occurs in the following chain:\n\n1. In raft/raft.go, the sendAppend() function (around line 440) attempts to send log entries to a follower node.\n\n2. When sending entries, it first calls raftLog.entries(pr.Next, r.maxMsgSize) (line 441) and raftLog.term(pr.Next - 1) (line 440) to retrieve the required entries.\n\n3. If an error occurs getting the entries or term (line 446), the leader determines it must send a snapshot instead (line 452).\n\n4. The leader calls raftLog.snapshot() (line 453) to get the snapshot to send. This function is defined in raft/log.go (lines 204-209) and retrieves either an unstable snapshot or calls storage.Snapshot().\n\n5. If storage.Snapshot() returns ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable (line 455), the sendAppend() function logs a debug message (line 456) and returns false (line 457), preventing the snapshot from being sent at that moment.\n\n6. The log retrieval through the slice() function in raft/log.go (lines 340-378) handles the case where requested entries have been compacted. When lo < unstable.offset (line 349), it calls storage.Entries(lo, min(hi, unstable.offset), maxSize) (line 350). If this returns ErrCompacted (line 351), the raftLog must use a snapshot to help the follower catch up.\n\nThe error scenario during node rejoin occurs when:\n- A node rejoins a cluster after being offline\n- The cluster has compacted log entries beyond the node's last known index\n- The leader must send a snapshot for the node to catch up (because entries before a certain index have been removed)\n- The snapshot is temporarily unavailable, causing the rejoin to fail with ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable\n\nRelated compaction logic is in server/etcdserver/server.go (lines 2498-2512) where snapshot catch-up entries are preserved to allow slow followers to catch up after snapshots are applied."
}

